column4: I can't run gnome-panel, whenever I do it says: I've detected a panel already running and will now exit, or something.
why are you trying to run it?
I have no panel applications running.
I logged in and it gave me the error message.
do you see a panel right now?
Can you break that down and explain? Just for future reference?
ps lists processes, and then you pipe with | to grep to search for the word "gnome-panel"
does this happen everytime or is this the first?
Edgy, in case you were wondering.
I remember you taught me that trick this past summer. I just forgot about it. :P
